main event: On January 9, 1965, a reported sighting of an unidentified flying object was documented at Mather AFB, California.
interesting points: The observation lasted between 5 to 10 seconds., The UFO was described as circular and grapefruit-shaped., It emitted a green glow during its descent., Witnesses stated the object floated and appeared to disintegrate before hitting the ground., There were two reliable witnesses: SSGT Joseph A. Schulze and A3C John W. Paxton, Jr.
witness description: SSGT Joseph A. Schulze, Senior Controller; A3C John W. Paxton, Jr, Air Traffic Controller
